observer (1.0.8) testing; urgency=medium

  * Add eight UI themes—innocent, maiden, girl, morandi, github, ios, msdos, and
    windows—and a shared palette for the observation prompt and statistics
    window; -t/--theme now accepts exact theme names.
  * Restyle statistics with theme colours, glass-style day summary and metric
    cards, a framed record table, and centered column headers.
  * Improve the observation prompt layout: wrap quotes at closing punctuation,
    balance line breaks, cap quote width, and size the window toward a golden
    ratio; prefer Chinese serif fonts for quotes and activity input.
  * Fix EMG rating labels overlapping their knobs; tune panel fills and rating
    ring colours per theme.
  * Click a quote to ask an AI assistant: launch DeepSeek on zh_CN with Doubao
    as fallback, or open Google AI mode search for other locales.
  * Add an embedded DeepSeek browser (--deepseek-browser) with WebKit disk
    cache, captcha-friendly settings, and automatic prompt submission after the
    chat page loads.
  * Add --diag to write observation dialog layout metrics to layout.toml and
    exit.
  * Expand oremind.bash completion for new themes and flags; refresh locale
    catalogs; link oremind against wxWebView and update Debian build
    dependencies.

